    "body": "+1 — filed a duplicate (#44037) before finding this one. Closing mine in favour of this.\n\nOur case: the companion (Lattice) noticed that 4 students in a batch of 86 AI-scored assignments received identical weighted totals (87.3). Investigation revealed 17 students had duplicate score vectors — the scoring model was collapsing to attractor values. The companion caught the pattern before the main Claude instance did, but the user had to screenshot the bubble and paste it into the conversation for it to be actionable.\n\nThe companion is doing genuine second-observer work. The lack of persistence and feedback channel means that value is lost unless the human manually bridges it.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
