    "updated_at": "2026-04-07T06:03:27Z",
    "body": "Follow-up: the linked \"cinder-capture\" repo has been updated since I filed this issue, and the current release (\"v0.2.0\") supersedes the original PoC description in the report.\n\nThe original report described the then-current workaround, which was centered on \"Stop\"-hook-based capture. In \"v0.2.0\", I confirmed that \"inject.py\" can write plain text to stdout from a command-type \"UserPromptSubmit\" hook and have that text folded into the next turn as context, so working auto-injection is now in place. The release also corrects my earlier assumption that command-type hooks could not inject \"additionalContext\".\n\n\"v0.2.0\" also changes the delivery model in a meaningful way: instead of reading only the latest captured entry, it now delivers all entries after the watermark within the configured age window, giving the prototype queue semantics rather than single-entry replay.\n\nThat changes the workaround details, but not the core request in this issue. Companion output is still UI-visible while remaining outside supported data paths: it is not exposed through a dedicated hook event, not available through a supported interface, and still has to be recovered from the render layer rather than accessed natively through logs or hook context.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
